[09:20] <zev> do you know why the second say fails here: http://paste.husk.org/10948
[09:21] <jonathan> get_global $P11, "foo"
[09:21] <jonathan> new $P11, "Integer"
[09:22] <zev> I don't understand
[09:22] <jonathan> That looks very...wrong... Because here $P11 is immediately overwritten with a new Integer PMC.
[09:22] <jonathan> So the first time you do a get_global, but immediately that register is used for something else.
[09:23] <jonathan> So you never end up giving what get_global returns to say that time.
[09:23] <zev> but shouldn't the new be making "foo" an Integer?
[09:23] <jonathan> No.
[09:23] <jonathan> For that you need to make a new integer, then do a set_global somewhere to see foo to be the new integer.
[09:23] <zev> I was under the impression that get_global makes the named register and the named name aliases for eachother
[09:24] <zev> oh, hrm
[09:24] <jonathan> No; get_global just does the lookup in the namespace.
[09:24] <jonathan> And gives you what it finds in that register.
[09:24] <zev> alright.  thanks
[09:24] <zev> have fun sightseeing!
[09:24] <jonathan> welcome.
